TITLE: Simplified Type Converter Using JsonTypeConverter
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a simplified approach where the type converter is defined as part of the data class itself, using JsonTypeConverter to ensure the converter works for both database and JSON serialization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/type_converters.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
@JsonSerializable()
class Preferences {
  final bool receiveEmails;
  final bool darkTheme;

  const Preferences({this.receiveEmails = false, this.darkTheme = true});

  factory Preferences.fromJson(Map<String, Object?> json) =>
      _$PreferencesFromJson(json);
  Map<String, Object?> toJson() => _$PreferencesToJson(this);

  // This converter will be used by drift when reading this class from a
  // database row, but also when serializing the class to json.
  static JsonTypeConverter<Preferences, String> converter =
      JsonTypeConverter.json(
    fromJson: (json) => Preferences.fromJson(json as Map<String, Object?>),
    toJson: (preferences) => preferences.toJson(),
  );
}
```

