TITLE: Multiple Table Joins in Drift
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to join multiple tables in a single query, finding related todo entries in the same category as a given entry.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/select.md#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
// loads all todo entries in the same category as the entry with the given id, but
// excluding the entry itself
Stream<List<TypedResult>> otherTodosInSameCategory(int idOfTodo) {
  final categoriesOfFirstEntry = select(categories).join([
    innerJoin(todos, todos.category.equalsExp(categories.id),
        where: todos.id.equals(idOfTodo)),
  ]);

  final asTempTable = categoriesOfFirstEntry.asJoinableTable();

  return select(todos)
      .join([
        innerJoin(asTempTable, asTempTable.$5.equalsExp(todos.category)),
      ])
      .where(todos.id.isNotEqual(idOfTodo))
      .watch();
}
```

