TITLE: Implementing database constructor for Flutter with sqlite3
DESCRIPTION: Database implementation for Flutter applications using sqlite3. Uses LazyDatabase to find the right location for the database file asynchronously in the application documents directory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/setup.md#2025-04-17_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
AppDatabase() : super(_openConnection());

// the LazyDatabase util lets us find the right location for the file async.
static LazyDatabase _openConnection() {
  // put the database file, called db.sqlite here, into the documents folder
  // for your app.
  return LazyDatabase(() async {
    final dbFolder = await getApplicationDocumentsDirectory();
    final file = File(p.join(dbFolder.path, 'db.sqlite'));

    return NativeDatabase.createInBackground(file);
  });
}
```

