TITLE: Ordering Query Results in Drift
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to order query results by one or more columns using the orderBy method, demonstrating both ascending and descending order options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/select.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
// Orders entries by their due date which defaults to ascending order
Stream<List<TodoEntry>> watchEntriesSortedByDueDate() {
  return (select(todos)..orderBy([(t) => OrderingTerm(expression: t.dueDate)])).watch();
}

// Returns entries that are sorted by both urgency and due date with equal urgencies
// put earlier
Future<List<TodoEntry>> sortedByUrgency() {
  return (select(todos)
    ..orderBy([
      (t) => OrderingTerm(expression: t.priority, mode: OrderingMode.desc),
      (t) => OrderingTerm(expression: t.dueDate),
    ])).get();
}
```

