TITLE: Deleting Category with Transaction in Dart using Drift
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to use a transaction to safely delete a category while moving associated todo entries to a default category. Demonstrates proper transaction usage with multiple atomic operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/transactions.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
Future<void> deleteCategory(Category category) {
  return transaction(() async {
    // First, move all entries in the category we're about to delete into the
    // default category
    await (update(todos)..where((t) => t.category.equals(category.id)))
        .write(TodosCompanion(category: Value(Category.defaultId)));

    // Then, delete the category itself
    await delete(categories).delete(category);
  });
}
```

