TITLE: Setting Up Custom Functions for Drift Database on Web
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to set up custom SQL functions for a Drift database running on the web using a custom worker.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/Platforms/web.md#2025-04-17_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
import 'package:drift/web.dart';

void main() {
  workerMainForOpen((openingRequest) {
    return setupAllDatabases(openingRequest);
  });
}

Future<void> setupAllDatabases(DriftWorkerRequest openingRequest) async {
  await openingRequest.resolvedExecutor.runCustom<void>((rawExecutor) {
    rawExecutor.createFunction(
      functionName: 'my_custom_function',
      function: (args) => 'Hello from WASM',
    );
  });
}
```

