TITLE: Configuring Drift for Flutter Web
DESCRIPTION: Code for configuring drift in a Flutter application for web support by setting up DriftWebOptions with paths to WebAssembly and worker files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/Platforms/web.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
final db = AppDatabase(
  connectToDriftWebDatabase(
    // This is the name of your web database. It will be stored in the
    // IndexedDB with that name.
    databaseName: 'my_app_database',
    // Additional options for web databases.
    webOptions: DriftWebOptions(
      // This option only applies to drift's wasm implementation. If
      // your app currently uses `sqlite3_flutter_libs` + `moor_flutter`
      // (e.g. you're migrating from an old version), make sure to remove
      // those packages when moving to web support.

      // Use a web worker instead of the main thread.
      useWorker: true,
      // The path to the worker JavaScript file (relative to your apps HTML file).
      // The file will be served from web/drift_worker.dart.js, which is created by
      // running the Dart-to-JS compiler on the worker defined in the
      // worker_support.dart Dart file.
      driftWorkerUri: 'drift_worker.dart.js',
    ),
  ),
);
```

