TITLE: Nested Transactions Example in Dart using Drift
DESCRIPTION: Demonstration of nested transactions behavior, showing how changes are isolated between transaction levels and how exceptions affect transaction state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/transactions.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
Future<void> example(Database db) async {
  await db.transaction(() async {
    print('in outer transaction');
    await db.into(db.todos).insert(TodosCompanion.insert(content: 'first'));

    try {
      await db.transaction(() async {
        print('in nested transaction');
        await db.into(db.todos).insert(
            TodosCompanion.insert(content: 'only visible in nested'));
        throw Exception('roll back nested transaction');
      });
    } catch (e) {
      print('caught: $e');
    }

    // At this point, the second insert was never visible to this transaction
    final amount = await db.select(db.todos).get();
    print('todos in outer transaction: $amount');
  });
}
```

