TITLE: Using Compound Selects for Category Item Counts in Drift
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use compound selects with UNION ALL to combine the results of multiple queries. This example counts items in each category plus items without a category in a single result set.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/select.md#2025-04-17_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
Future<List<CategoryWithCount>> compound() {
  // Returns rows of form (category_description, count).
  // The first query includes all categories with associated items (counting the
  // items), the second query adds a (NULL, count) row for items without a category
  final firstQuery = (select(categories)..addColumns([todos.id.count()]))
      .join([innerJoin(todos, todos.category.equalsExp(categories.id))])
      .groupBy([categories.id])
      .map((row) {
        return CategoryWithCount(
          category: Category.fromData(row.readTable(categories)),
          count: row.read(todos.id.count()) ?? 0,
        );
      });

  final secondQuery = selectOnly(todos)
    ..addColumns([todos.id.count()])
    ..where(todos.category.isNull())
    ..map((row) => CategoryWithCount(
          category: null,
          count: row.read(todos.id.count()) ?? 0,
        ));

  return firstQuery.unionAll(secondQuery).get();
}
```

