TITLE: Using Subqueries to Count Top-10 Todo Items in Each Category in Drift
DESCRIPTION: A demonstration of using the Subquery feature to join complex query results. This example counts how many of the top-10 longest todo items belong to each category by first creating a subquery and then joining it to the main query.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/select.md#2025-04-17_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
Future<List<CategoryWithCount>> subquery() {
  // First, create a query for the top 10 todos by length
  final top10 = select(todos)
    ..orderBy([(t) => OrderingTerm.desc(t.title.length)])
    ..limit(10);

  // Now, create a larger query grouping todos by category
  return (select(categories)..addColumns([todos.id.count()]))
      .join([
        leftOuterJoin(
          todos,
          todos.category.equalsExp(categories.id),
        ),
        // Join the top10 subquery to only include todos that are also in the top 10
        innerJoin(
          Subquery(top10, 'top10'),
          todos.id.equalsExp(Subquery(top10, 'top10').ref(todos.id)),
          useColumns: false,
        )
      ])
      .groupBy([categories.id])
      .map((row) {
        return CategoryWithCount(
          category: Category.fromData(row.readTable(categories)),
          count: row.read(todos.id.count()),
        );
      })
      .get();
}
```

