TITLE: Watching a Single Cart with RxDart in Relational Model
DESCRIPTION: Implements a method to watch a shopping cart and its items using RxDart's combineLatest2 to merge streams of cart data and cart entries into a single CartWithItems object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/Examples/relationships.md#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
@override
Stream<CartWithItems> watchCart(int id) {
  // First, create a stream of cart entries. We join the BuyableItems table
  // to include information about the product
  final entriesQuery = select(cartEntries).join([
    innerJoin(buyableItems, cartEntries.product.equalsExp(buyableItems.id)),
  ]);
  entriesQuery.where(cartEntries.cart.equals(id));

  // Then, create a stream of the cart itself
  final cartQuery = select(shoppingCarts)..where((c) => c.id.equals(id));

  // Finally, we use the `combineLatest2` feature from the rxdart package to wait
  // for both streams to emit a value, and then we combine the two results into a
  // CartWithItems object
  return Rx.combineLatest2(
    cartQuery.watchSingle(),
    entriesQuery.watch(),
    (ShoppingCart cart, List<TypedResult> entries) {
      // For each entry, extract the joined buyable item and the amount
      final items = entries.map((row) {
        final product = row.readTable(buyableItems);
        final entry = row.readTable(cartEntries);

        final buyable = BuyableItem(
          id: product.id,
          name: product.name,
          image: product.image,
          price: product.price,
        );

        return CartItem(item: buyable, amount: entry.amount);
      }).toList();

      return CartWithItems(
        id: cart.id,
        createdAt: cart.createdAt,
        items: items,
      );
    },
  );
}
```

