TITLE: Migrating Existing Database to Encryption in Dart
DESCRIPTION: Function to migrate an existing unencrypted database to an encrypted one using SQLCipher, following the recommended steps for encryption migration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/Platforms/encryption.md#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
Future<void> migrateToEncryption(String path) async {
  final database = sqlite3.open(path);

  // Create a new, encrypted database file
  database.execute(
    "ATTACH DATABASE '$path.encrypted' AS encrypted KEY 'my_password';",
  );

  // Copy all data from the unencrypted database to the new one
  database.execute('SELECT sqlcipher_export("encrypted");');
  database.execute('DETACH DATABASE encrypted;');

  database.dispose();

  // Delete the old, unencrypted database
  await File(path).delete();
  // Rename the encrypted database to match the old file name
  await File('$path.encrypted').rename(path);
}

// Use this in your app like this:
final database = await NativeDatabase.createInBackground(
  await getDatabasesPath(),
  setup: (db) {
    db.execute("PRAGMA key = 'my_password';");
  },
  isolateSetup: () async {
    await setupSqlCipher();
    BackgroundIsolateBinaryMessenger.ensureInitialized();

    final dbPath = await getDatabasePath();
    await migrateToEncryption(dbPath);
  },
);
```

