TITLE: Implementing Custom Row Values Expression in Drift
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement the Expression interface directly to create a custom expression for SQLite row values. This advanced approach provides complete control over how the SQL is generated.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/expressions.md#2025-04-17_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
class RowValues<T extends ResultSetImplementation> implements Expression {
  final List<Expression> _expressions;

  RowValues(this._expressions);

  @override
  final bool? restrictions = null;

  @override
  Precedence get precedence => Precedence.primary;

  @override
  void writeInto(GenerationContext context) {
    context.buffer.write('(');
    var first = true;
    for (final expression in _expressions) {
      if (!first) {
        context.buffer.write(', ');
      } else {
        first = false;
      }

      expression.writeInto(context);
    }
    context.buffer.write(')');
  }
}
```

