TITLE: Joining Calls with Contacts using JSON_EACH in Drift
DESCRIPTION: A complex query that matches call records with contacts by using JSON_EACH to expand the phone numbers array from each contact's JSON data, enabling a join between calls and the appropriate contact.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/dart_api/select.md#2025-04-17_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
Future<List<CallWithContact>> getCallsWithContacts() {
  // This query will find the contact for each call, if there's any with a
  // matching phone number.

  // We can't join calls and contacts directly since the phone numbers are stored
  // in a JSON array. json_each can be used to expand the array into a table where
  // each array element becomes a row.
  final expandedNumbers = jsonEach(contacts.contact.dartCast<String>(),
      '$.phoneNumbers')
      .asExpression()
      .as('expanded');

  return (select(calls)
        ..addColumns([contacts.contact]))
      .join([
        leftOuterJoin(
          expandedNumbers,
          calls.phoneNumber.equals(expandedNumbers.ref('value').dartCast<String>()),
          useColumns: false,
        ),
        // The previous join used the expanded array. Now, find the contact that this
        // array belongs to
        leftOuterJoin(contacts,
            contacts.id.equalsExp(expandedNumbers.ref('id').dartCast<int>()))
      ])
      .map(
        (row) => CallWithContact(
          call: Call.fromData(row.readTable(calls)),
          contact: row.read(contacts.contact),
        ),
      )
      .get();
}
```

