TITLE: Using Dialect-Aware DateTime Columns for Cross-Database Compatibility
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to create dialect-aware datetime columns that work with both SQLite and PostgreSQL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/simolus3/drift/blob/develop/docs/docs/Platforms/postgres.md#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
class Events extends Table {
  IntColumn get id => integer().autoIncrement()();

  // Will use a TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE in postgres, datetime in sqlite
  Column<DateTime> get createdAt => customType(
        DialectSpecificType(
          sqliteType: drift.DateTimeType(),
          postgresType: PgTypes.timestamptz,
        ),
